benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/overdue - Retrieve overdue state for account

covered: Valid Request: 200 responses and OverdueState validation for valid accounts (TC01, TC02).
Authorization: 401 errors for missing or invalid tokens (TC07, TC08).
Not Found / Empty Data: 404 when account not found (TC03) and 404 when database is empty (TC13).
Input Validation & Security: 400 responses for invalid/malformed accountId; includes tests for injection and XSS (TC04, TC05, TC06, TC10, TC11, TC16).
Query Parameters: Extra query parameters are ignored (TC12).

Performance & Resilience: 200 with performance checks (TC14), concurrency (TC15), large payload (TC18), transient network recovery (TC19), dependency degradation handling (TC17) and backward compatibility (TC20).
gaps: Pagination: Not applicable for single-resource GET; no pagination tests needed.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting/throttling (429).
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or conditional requests.
Observability/Logging: No tests validating traces/logs across services or error message consistency beyond HTTP status.
recommendations: Add pagination handling guidance if the endpoint grows to return multiple items; otherwise explicitly mark as not applicable.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to validate 429 responses under burst traffic.
Add caching tests for ETag and Cache-Control headers and for conditional requests (If-Modified-Since, If-None-Match).
Add observability tests for tracing/logging across service boundaries to help diagnose failures.
